                <head>No. 48.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Gresham</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Baker</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-05-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 12, 1894</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received your report in regard to the
                    situation at Blue-fields of May 2.</p>
                <p>The matter is under careful consideration, and in due time you will be fully
                    instructed. Meanwhile you should take care to say nothing tending to disparage
                    Nicaragua’s rightful claim to paramount sovereignty or to encourage pretentions
                    to autonomous rights inconsistent therewith.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. Q. Gresham.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
